      "message": "The \"number \u003d bit_cast\u003cType\u003e(i)\" line is problematic. For any template instantiation, only one of the if-branches is able to compile:\n\nIn file included from ../../util/linux/memory_map.cc:23:\n../../third_party/mini_chromium/mini_chromium/base/bit_cast.h:64:3: error: static_assert failed \"bit_cast requires source and destination to be the same size\"\n  static_assert(sizeof(Dest) \u003d\u003d sizeof(Source),\n  ^             ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~\n../../util/linux/memory_map.cc:51:15: note: in instantiation of function template specialization \u0027bit_cast\u003clong, unsigned int\u003e\u0027 requested here\n    *number \u003d bit_cast\u003cType\u003e(i);",
